reviewText: I have a lot of workout DVDs, and bought this one because Valerie has inspired me. However, I am not a fan of this product. The DVD is two workouts, one 20-minute beginner and one 30-minute bikini workout. First of all, I do not like the trainer in this video. He is not very relatable and just seems a bit odd to me. Second, this video is mostly lower body work - I would say well over half is lunges and squats. Lastly, while I love Valerie and find her completely relatable and sweet, the cueing is not great. She and the trainer go different directions and aren't completely on the same page. This is one workout DVD I wish I hadn't purchased!
Title: N/A

reviewText: It's hard to believe that Valerie Bertinelli is in her 50's and had ever struggled with weight problems. She looks great.Her sunny personality and upbeat attitude shines through (as usual) in this exercise DVD. You can't help but feel enthused about following along and Losing It too!Unlike so many other exercise dvds, Valerie actually makes working out fun. And before you know it, it's a done deal!Keep them coming Val, you are an inspiration to all of us! :<)
Title: N/A

reviewText: I really like this workout.  It's not too grueling for my age but does give me a good workout.  Their "slow" moves are different than my "slow" moves, but otherwise it's really good.However, as much as I like Valarie Bertinelli, she does way too much "cutsie" chatter during the workout.  It wasn't too bad the first few times I exercised but now I dread hearing her constant comments.  I guess she wants some input as it is her workout dvd, but boy it gets old fast.Otherwise, I'd recommend it for someone who is getting back to exercising, like me, and/or a senior, like me.

reviewText: I got this DVD mainly because of Valerie Bertinelli. She's down to earth to exercise with. Ijust started the tape and I'm doing Level 1 for starters. It's NOT challenging for the ABS, AT ALL, I'm disappointed in that.Otherwise, I like it.

reviewText: Valerie giggles as she works out making this a very fun & upbeat video for beginners.My Dr. said I need both knees replaced & I'm doing everything to get into shape _without_ surgery. I was able to do this video without stressing my knees. YAY!

reviewText: I love this DVD workout.My legs were so sore the next day and the AB workout was great because it gets the job done in the least amount of time. The bonus is you dont have to have a lot of time to do the workout. On days I want more (have more time and more energy)I just do it twice and that really works you. One of my new favs!!!

reviewText: This workout is wonderful. Valerie & training coach, Chris, light bantering make this workout fun, but don't let that fool you by the end of both workouts Chris has worked you from head to toe .  I hope Valerie has more of these workouts to come.
